It would be nice to have an option for _JIRA Administrators_ or _Service Desk Agents_ to create _Service Desk Customers_ without the need to send an invitation e-mail.

h4. Workaround
For now, the only way to do so without the invite is through the default user creation in JIRA.
# Go to *Administration* > *User Management*;
# Hit *Create Users* in the top right of the page;
# Fill the form with user's details;
(i) Uncheck "Send Notification Email".
# Create the user;
# On the right of the newly-created user, click *Groups*;
# Add groups you want to have the user included;
(i) If you do not want the customer to access JIRA itself, remove it from the {{jira-users}} group (valid for JIRA instances with "default" schemes)
# Open up the *Project Administration* page for the Service Desk Project you want the user to be added;
# Go to *Roles* (on the sidebar);
# Add the user to *Service Desk Customers* role;
(!) Note that this will only work if you use the new Service Desk licensing model (unlimited customers).

